notes.body:
Dextromethorphan (DEX) liver model
DEX can be taken up by the liver and be converted to DOR via CYP2D6. This reaction can be inhibited by substances such as quinidine. Within the liver part of the DEX can be metabolized via CYP3A4 mediated first-pass metabolism (this reaction and the metabolic product of the reaction MEM is not part of the model).

parameter.name: A factor used to scan DEXCYP2D6_Km (for induction and inhibition)

First eigen value of (Vmax, Km) in log space. Determies how much Km should be scaled if Vmax is scaled. In this model Vmax is scalled by the activity score. The value was calculated based on Storelli2019 and Yang2012.

body.p: Complex reaction kinetics by CYP2D6. Reaction kinetics contains competitive inhibition by quinidine, is affected by CYP2D6 activity score. Competitive inhibition via quinidine.

This reaction is required for the poor metabolizer phenotype, which have no CYP2D6 activity. A basal low conversion exists independent of CYP2D6 phenotype. 2021-09-08|janekg: CYP mediated conversion of DEX to DOR normally accounting for a low percentage of conversion.
